Isiolo County Residents are mourning the brutal murder of a 45-year-old environmentalist, human rights activist and peace crusader who was stabbed to death while she attended a burial ceremony at Kambi Garba area.
According to her nephew Philemon Ekwam who was also attending the burial, Elizabeth Ibrahim was called by a familiar person and she followed him to a nearby disputed farm, where the man struck, stabbing her eight times and killing her on the spot.